Assume we have following samples:
String fileName = "//host/folder/image.txt";
URL url = new File(fileName).toURL();
String fileUrl = url.toString();
URL url2 = new URL(fileUrl);
String fileUrl2 = url2.toString();

althrough the fileUrl and fileUrl2 is equals (file://host/folder/image.txt), the object url is not equals to url2.
url.getHost() == null
url2.getHost() == host
url.getFile() == //host/folder/image.txt
url2.getFile() == /folder/image.txt.

So, if the user uses the file path, the path should be:
"\\\\host\\folder\\file.name"
If the user uses the file URL, the URL should be:
"file:////host/folder/file.name"

